@startuml accel_brake_longitudinal_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Accel Brake Longitudinal Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> VCU -> ESC -> EHB / VSM -> CLU)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Pedal + Cruise" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "VCU\nmanual target + speed owner" as VCU #E8F7E8
participant "ESC\nbrake pressure owner" as ESC #FFE6E6
participant "EHB\nhydraulic brake state" as EHB #FFF4CC
participant "VSM\nstability intervention view" as VSM #FCE8FF
participant "CLU\nspeed / brake readback" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Driver Longitudinal Input ==

Driver -> Panel : Press ACCEL / BRAKE\nor choose speed preset / cruise set
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Cmd::throttlePedalPct\nWrite Cmd::brakePedalPct
Panel -> Panel : Optional Cmd::vehicleSpeedCmd\nOptional Powertrain::cruiseSetSpeed
note right of Panel
Primary seams
- Cmd::throttlePedalPct
- Cmd::brakePedalPct
- Cmd::vehicleSpeedCmd
- Cmd::driveStateCmd
- Powertrain::cruiseState / cruiseSetSpeed
end note
deactivate Panel

== VCU Manual Longitudinal Ownership ==

activate VCU
Panel -> VCU : Cmd::* longitudinal seams
VCU -> VCU : latch manual drive/speed target\nwhen scenarioActiveId == 0
VCU -> VCU : owner vehicle dynamics lead\nonce pedal input arrives
VCU -> VCU : derive engineState / driveState / speed
VCU -> ESC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
VCU -> ESC : frmWheelPulseMsg
VCU -> VSM : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
VCU -> CLU : Chassis::vehicleSpeed / driveState readback
note right of VCU
Representative owner logic
- gManualVehicleSpeedTarget
- manualCruiseActive
- externalSpeedOverride
- output frmVehicleStateCanMsg / frmWheelPulseMsg
end note
deactivate VCU

== ESC Brake Pressure Ownership ==

activate ESC
Panel -> ESC : Cmd::brakePedalPct
VCU -> ESC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
ESC -> ESC : appliedBrakePedal = Cmd::brakePedalPct\nmanual mode
ESC -> ESC : Chassis::brakePressure = appliedBrakePedal
ESC -> ESC : brakeLamp / absActive / espActive
ESC -> EHB : frmBrakeStatusMsg
ESC -> VSM : frmEscStateMsg
ESC -> CLU : Chassis::brakePressure / brakeLamp / absActive
note right of ESC
Published outputs
- frmBrakeStatusMsg
- frmEscStateMsg
- Chassis::brakePressure
- Chassis::brakeLamp
end note
deactivate ESC

== Brake / Stability Downstream ==

activate EHB
ESC -> EHB : frmBrakeStatusMsg
EHB -> EHB : derive pressureCmd / ctrlState
EHB -> EHB : output frmEhbStateMsg
deactivate EHB

activate VSM
ESC -> VSM : frmEscStateMsg
VCU -> VSM : frmVehicleStateCanMsg
VSM -> VSM : derive intervention / alert level
VSM -> VSM : output frmVsmStateMsg
deactivate VSM

== Visible Outcome ==

activate CLU
VCU -> CLU : Chassis::vehicleSpeed
ESC -> CLU : Chassis::brakePressure
CLU -> Panel : speed / brake readback
deactivate CLU

Driver <- Panel : Speed, meter, brake response move together

note over Driver, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. Driver sets accel / brake / speed aid from Input_Console
2. VCU owns speed / drive-state dynamics
3. ESC owns brake pressure and brake status
4. EHB and VSM consume brake / vehicle state downstream
5. CLU and Input_Console show speed/brake readback
end note

@enduml
